<p style="text-align:left;"><strong><u>How We Protect Your Personal Data</u></strong><br>We take the security of your data seriously. To protect your personal information, we use industry-standard encryption for data at rest and in transit. Access to our database is secured with strong authentication protocols, including role-based access control (RBAC) and multi-factor authentication (MFA). We also restrict access through IP whitelisting and secure our network with firewalls and VPNs. Regular backups are encrypted, and we maintain audit logs to monitor activities. Our system is kept up to date with the latest security patches, and we ensure that all user input is validated to prevent unauthorized access. By following these best practices, we work to safeguard your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or loss.<br><br>While we take all reasonable precautions to ensure that user data is secure and that users are protected, there always remains the risk of harm. The Internet as a whole can be insecure at times and therefore we are unable to guarantee the security of user data beyond what is reasonably practical.
</p>
